        <name xml:lang="en">Water</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">m3</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value. The value is calculated as the sum of water input minus wastewater, times fraction going to ait (8%) or to water (92%). Assumption of amount of wastewater and of fraction goinf to air and water are from a generic model. The basic principles of the model have been published in literature (Hischier 2005, Establishing Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals Based on Differing Data Availability). The model has been updated and extended with newly available data from the chemical industry. Find more information in the dedicated report on the ecoinvent website. 

Reference(s):
Hischier, R. (2005) Establishing Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals Based on Differing Data Availability (9 pp). The International Journal of Life Cycle Assessment, Volume 10, Issue 1, pp 59–67. 10.1065/lca2004.10.181.7
</comment>
